items.name: obscura-intent-mesh
items.description: Speak a goal → prove eligibility privately → route it across chains with obfuscated execution.

items.name: taproot-script-demo
items.description: Taproot script-path spend demo in TypeScript. Implements tagged hashing, TapLeaf/TapBranch/TapTweak, key tweak (internal→output), control block build, and a minimal <xonly_pub> OP_CHECKSIG leaf. BIP340 Schnorr via noble. Educational only.

items.name: real-estate-roi-lab
items.description: ROI toolkit for rental properties — cap rate, cash-on-cash, IRR, amortization, DSCR, and sensitivity tables. Comes with a Streamlit dashboard and a small Python API. Educational use.

items.name: aa-session-keys-demo
items.description: Minimal ERC-4337-style smart account with session keys and rate limits, plus a tiny Next.js dApp to grant/revoke per-dApp permissions and call a target via a session key. Educational demo (no full bundler).

items.name: musig2-toy
items.description: Educational MuSig2-style Schnorr multisignatures over secp256k1 using noble-curves. Key aggregation, nonce aggregation, partial signatures, and aggregate verification — with a CLI + tests. Not production code.

items.name: confidential-intent-sim
items.description: A TypeScript monorepo simulating private intent execution with opaque state. Users express natural language goals, which are translated into encrypted actions and routed through a solver network. Educational toy model for intent-centric DeFi privacy.

items.name: merkle-airdrop-studio
items.description: End-to-end toolkit for Merkle airdrops: build a tree from CSV/JSON, generate proofs, verify locally and on-chain, and ship a tiny web proof checker. Includes a Solidity claim contract, TS CLI, and Foundry tests. Educational—not audited.

items.name: merkle-airdrop-studio-erc20
items.description: ERC-20 Merkle airdrop toolkit: build a Merkle root & per-address proofs from CSV/JSON, deploy an ERC-20 claim contract, and verify proofs with a TS CLI or a tiny web checker. Includes Foundry tests. Educational—not audited.

items.name: poseidon-merkle-gadget
items.description: Poseidon-based Merkle tree (BN254) in TypeScript: toy Poseidon (t=3) permutation, tree build, inclusion proofs, and verifier—meant as a “zk gadget” scaffold to plug into circuits later. Not a zk proof system; educational.

items.name: dex-subgraph-starter
items.description: Starter subgraph for a Uniswap V2–style DEX plus a tiny web viewer. Indexes a Pair’s Swap/Sync events, tracks reserves & basic volume, and exposes them via GraphQL. Ready to codegen, build, and deploy on The Graph.
